    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A soft, plastic, non-drying, claylike substance, used for modelling. The original was invented by William Harbutt, an English art teacher, in 1897. There are various formulations made from calcium salts, petroleum jelly, and aliphatic acids.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000114707/Oxford English Dictionary Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Un material arcilloso suave y maleable empleado para modelar. Está compuesto de sales de calcio, jalea de petróleo y ácidos alifáticos. Fue inventada por William Harbutt, un profesor de arte inglés, en 1897.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>一種柔軟、可塑、黏土狀的物質，用來做模型。是由鈣鹽、凡士林及脂肪酸所製成。1897年時，由一位名為威廉‧哈伯特（William Harbutt）的英格蘭藝術教師所發明。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052784/TELDAP database (2009-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Een zachte, plastic, kleiachtige stof die wordt gebruikt om te boetseren. Hij is gemaakt van calciumzouten, petrolatum en alifatische zuren. Plasticine werd in 1897 uitgevonden door William Harbutt, een Engelse kunstdocent.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
